title: X Factor: Celebrity live shows line-up revealed as Jenny Ryan is knocked out
text:
Who is through to the X Factor: Celebrity live shows? (Picture: ITV)

X Factor: Celebrity has revealed their official line-up for the live shows, featuring some surprising decisions.

The latest episode saw judges Simon Cowell, Louis Walsh, and Nicole Scherzinger whittle down the contestants to eleven acts following their first audition in Los Angeles.

So who has made it through to next week’s live shows? You can check out the results below.

X Factor: Celebrity live show line-up Simon Cowell – Groups Max And Harvey V5 Try Star Love Island supergroup Louis Walsh – Unders Jonny Labey Kevin McHale Olivia Olson Megan McKenna Nicole Scherzinger – Overs Victoria Ekanoye Ricki Lake Martin Bashir Vinnie Jones

The contestants rejected from the competition were duo Brendan Cole & Jeremy Edwards, Hayley Hasselhoff, and controversially, The Chase’s Jenny Ryan.

Vinnie Jones was also announced to be appearing at the live shows, after being forced to pull out of auditions due to the death of his wife Tanya.

The remaining acts are all competing for a record contract on Simon Cowell’s label, with hopes of actually building a music career from the show.

The first episode of the series saw the likes of a Love Island supergroup, comprised of Wes Nelson, Eyal Booker, Samira Mighty and Zara McDermott, The Chase’s Jenny Ryan and duo Jeremy Edwards and Brendan Cole audition.

In the second episode, Love, Actually star Olivia Olson took to the stage, alongside Megan McKenna and EastEnders actor Jonny Labey who played Paul Coker in the soap.

The X Factor: Celebrity live shows are set to kick off next Saturday in London, with the series set to be followed by a special all-stars edition too.

The X Factor: Celebrity continues next Saturday on ITV.
